Experimental problems.Objectives/eesmärkid:  *To give an overview of the organization and rules of physics olympiads. *To introduce the specifics and solving methods of lower secondary school physics olympiad problems and to give practical guidelines for preparing the pupils for participation. *To give the student experience of solving lower secondary school physics olympiad problems.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: 1. Can find and use information about physics olympiads. 2. Is able to find connections between lower secondary school olympiad and curriculum. 3. Knows ways of motivating pupils to participate in olympiads. 4. Has necessary prior knowledge needed for solving lower secondary physics olympiad problems and knows their solving methods. 5. Can solve lower secondary physics olympiad problems. 6. Has ideas of how to prepare pupils for lower secondary school physics olympiads.
